1. Install dependency

<pre> pip3 install pyAesCrypt </pre>

2. Save the script above as aes_bruteforce_mp.py and make executable:

<pre> chmod +x aes_bruteforce_mp.py </pre>

3. run
<pre> python3 aes_bruteforce_mp.py --aes backup.aes --wordlist /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt --out recovered_archive.zip --workers 6 --checkpoint .aes_ckpt --chunk 400 </pre>


* --workers tune to number of CPU cores (or fewer if disk/CPU thrashes).

* --chunk controls how many passwords are sent in a batch; smaller if you want more frequent checkpointing.

* If itâ€™s interrupted, re-run the same command and it will resume from the last checkpoint line.
